<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Ambassador in the Soviet Union (
                        Harriman
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v05</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d774</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">774</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-06-21T10:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-06-21T10:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-21T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-21T10:00:00-05:00" n="774" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d774">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/6–2145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-21T18:00:00+03:00">June 21, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 21—4:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2210. Personal for Harry Hopkins.<note n="82" xml:id="d774fn82">Chairman of the
                        President’s Soviet Protocol Committee.</note> Am gravely concerned over
                    delays in action on Russian Lend-Lease requests submitted while you were in
                        Moscow.<note n="83" xml:id="d774fn83">For documentation on the Hopkins
                        mission to Moscow, see <ref target="frus1945Berlinv01#pg_21">
                            <hi rend="italic">Conference of Berlin</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Potsdam</hi>), vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 21</ref>
                        ff.</note> Hope you can see Sid Spalding, now in Washington, and after
                    obtaining from him the facts and our recommendations do what you can to get
                    immediate action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
